2. The details mentioned in Annexure A such as carpet area, booking status, unit consideration, date of agreement to sale, encumbrance status, name, KYC and mobile numbers of allottees are as provided by the management. Amount received in case of few cancelled units have not been refunded and unidentified receipts are unaccounted in the books and hence are not considered in the Annexure. The certificate is addressed to and provided to the promoters of the project solely for the purpose to enable comply with requirement of RERA , and should not be used by any other person or for any other purpose. Accordingly, we do not accept or assume any liability or any duty of care for any other purpose or to any other person to whom this certificate is shown or into whose hands it may come without our prior consent in writing. 
5. Where lease deed has been registered directly, such date has been considered in the column of agreement to sale in annexure.	
6. Few units were previously booked and then re-booked after cancellation as per management. However, refund for cancelled units in few cases are not made. Details of new allottees are provided by the management in the Annexure.
